      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اِمْرَأَةٍ أَرَادَتْ أَنْ تُحْرِمَ فَتَخَوَّفَتِ اَلشُّقَاقَ تَخْضِبُ بِالْحِنَّاءِ قَبْلَ ذَلِكَ قَالَ «مَا يُعْجِبُنِي أَنْ تَفْعَلَ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2659 - Muhammad ibn al-Fudayl narrated from Abu al-Sabbah al-Kinani, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a woman who wished to enter Ihram but feared skin cracking. Could she apply henna beforehand?\nImam (as) said: \"I do not like for her to do so.\""
        ]
      }
